A Philistine border town in the northeast was Gbtn/Gab-bu-tú-nu/Γαββαθων, Γα/εβα/εθων (Tall Mlāṭ, now Tel Malot 14 km. north of Ekron, see Bagg, 2007, 68 with lit.), whereas nearby Gezer more to the east was Israelite. Gibbethon belonged to Ekron, the more so in view of the fact that Gab-bu-tú-nu is recorded in an epigraph of Sargon II, who seized Ekron https://s3.amazonaws.com/academia.edu.documents/31935699/UF-42-Zadok-offprint.pdf?AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAIWOWYYGZ2Y53UL3A&Expires=1529049875&Signature=TbA2wJxBF3m88ulh5vwhcHkbTAQ%3D&response-content-disposition=inline%3B%20filename%3DPhilistian_Notes_II.pdf p. 860 Philistian Notes II Ran Zadok *{{cite web|url=http://www.academia.edu/4557481/Philistian_Notes_II|title=Philistian Notes II &#124; Ran Zadok|website=Academia.edu|accessdate=2018-11-01}}
